WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
[indistinct chatter]

00:08.600 --> 00:10.600
[laughter]

00:14.080 --> 00:15.720
Right. Uh, certainly.

00:15.760 --> 00:17.360
-No. No, no, no.
-What?

00:17.400 --> 00:19.520
-No, you can't leave now. No.
-I have to go now.

00:19.560 --> 00:22.040
No, that would make you
officially boring.

00:22.080 --> 00:23.840
Just one more. Uno mas.
Georgia.

00:23.880 --> 00:25.600
GEORGIA:
Oh, you're awful women.

00:25.640 --> 00:27.280
-You're terrible people.
-All right, night, sir.

00:27.320 --> 00:30.480
-Night, sir.
-You're also both twats.

00:42.840 --> 00:44.840
[siren wails in distance]

00:54.160 --> 00:55.800
Hey.

00:57.760 --> 01:00.000
-Shh, shh, shh, shh.
-Oh, she's up.

01:00.040 --> 01:01.600
-Hey, Mumma's home.
-[baby coos]

01:04.440 --> 01:07.480
Mumma's here.

01:10.320 --> 01:14.080
-[baby whimpers]
-Oh, shh, shh, shh.

01:14.120 --> 01:15.840
How was your night?

01:15.880 --> 01:17.480
It was good.

01:17.520 --> 01:19.480
-I missed this little one,
though.
-Yeah.

01:19.520 --> 01:22.040
Hand her over.

01:22.080 --> 01:24.160
Hey. Here's Mumma.

01:24.200 --> 01:27.800
-Yeah.
-Baby.

01:27.840 --> 01:30.520
[baby coos]

01:30.560 --> 01:32.560
Shh.

01:32.600 --> 01:35.240
[quietly]:
"V" is for Violet.

01:35.280 --> 01:37.400
"V" is for
Violet.

01:37.440 --> 01:41.560
"V" is for very, very,
very valuable Violet.

01:41.600 --> 01:44.720
"V" is for Violet.

01:44.760 --> 01:49.440
"V" is for very,
very valuable Violet.

01:49.480 --> 01:50.640
Why does that work?

01:50.680 --> 01:53.440
I don't know.

01:57.760 --> 02:00.040
"B" is for beautiful.

02:06.480 --> 02:09.560
"G" is for go and make me
some food, I'm starving.

02:09.600 --> 02:12.440
Okay. [grunts]

02:22.240 --> 02:24.240
♪ ♪

02:27.360 --> 02:28.640
[woman speaking French]

02:28.680 --> 02:30.760
[woman continues
speaking French]

02:41.800 --> 02:43.880
[speaking French]

02:47.320 --> 02:49.120
We should go.

02:49.160 --> 02:52.120
What? A man is lying dead
in front of you,

02:52.160 --> 02:54.080
and you want us to pretend
it did not happen?

02:54.120 --> 02:55.840
What, would you had rather
I got in the truck with him?

02:57.880 --> 02:59.440
TOM:
Who are you?

02:59.480 --> 03:01.960
I'm out here looking for
someone. He's in Kisima.

03:04.680 --> 03:06.560
Look, w-we've been out
of contact. We need to get

03:06.600 --> 03:08.480
in touch with base,
let them know where we are,

03:08.520 --> 03:10.800
-Look, we can drive
God knows how far,
-and what our plans...

03:10.840 --> 03:12.680
to the nearest police station
and you can tell them I shot

03:12.720 --> 03:14.720
a man who was trying
to abduct me at gunpoint.

03:14.760 --> 03:17.080
Or you can do the job you came
here to do, and we can just go

03:17.120 --> 03:19.880
to Kisima. Either way, we're
fucking idiots if we stay here.

03:19.920 --> 03:21.920
[speaking French]

03:25.360 --> 03:26.640
Let's go.

03:26.680 --> 03:27.840
No, no, no, no.

03:27.880 --> 03:29.120
We better take this.

03:29.160 --> 03:31.600
[speaking French]

03:33.720 --> 03:35.960
[Fabrice continues speaking
French]

03:40.520 --> 03:43.520
[Fabrice and Louise continue
arguing in French]

03:43.560 --> 03:46.040
-Tom.
-TOM: Let's go.

03:47.160 --> 03:49.400
♪ ♪

04:00.080 --> 04:02.240
♪ ♪

04:19.120 --> 04:20.800
That's weird.

04:20.840 --> 04:22.040
What?

04:22.080 --> 04:23.480
Normally people
are so pleased to see us

04:23.520 --> 04:25.320
we can barely get
the doors open.

04:25.360 --> 04:27.440
Something's happened.

04:27.480 --> 04:28.640
This is Congo.

04:28.680 --> 04:30.240
Something has always happened.

04:32.040 --> 04:34.040
♪ ♪

04:46.440 --> 04:48.480
Welcome to Kisima.

04:48.520 --> 04:50.440
[scoffs] Thanks.

04:54.600 --> 04:56.760
[indistinct shouting]

04:58.600 --> 04:59.960
[speaking French]

05:00.000 --> 05:01.520
There were no reports
of militia on the radio.

05:01.560 --> 05:03.120
Well, I guess they were wrong.

05:03.160 --> 05:07.200
Okay. I'm going to go
talk to him.

05:07.240 --> 05:08.560
Hey, Fabrice, just...

05:08.600 --> 05:11.560
Ca va.So, okay.

05:11.600 --> 05:12.960
[speaking French]

05:13.000 --> 05:15.240
[Fabrice speaking French]

05:15.280 --> 05:17.160
[soldier speaking French]

05:17.200 --> 05:20.920
[speaking French]

05:34.160 --> 05:35.800
[sighs]

05:35.840 --> 05:37.280
I told them who we were.

05:37.320 --> 05:39.200
They said to carry on.

05:40.560 --> 05:42.000
Who are they with?

05:42.040 --> 05:43.400
The Mai-Mai.

05:43.440 --> 05:45.320
They started off
defending the territory

05:45.360 --> 05:46.640
from Rwandan militia.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.560
Some say they oppose
our government,

05:48.600 --> 05:50.760
but most of them left politics
a long time ago.

05:50.800 --> 05:54.040
This group? It's better not
to ask too many questions.

05:54.080 --> 05:56.400
[speaking French]

05:56.440 --> 05:58.960
What can I do?

05:59.000 --> 06:00.720
Okay.

06:00.760 --> 06:02.600
I thought you had
other business here.

06:02.640 --> 06:04.480
Yeah. I'm just offering to help.

06:04.520 --> 06:06.480
[Louise speaking French]

06:06.520 --> 06:08.240
We need our supplies inside.

06:08.280 --> 06:10.680
We need to make a space here
for anyone infected

06:10.720 --> 06:12.640
to be kept away
from the general population.

06:12.680 --> 06:14.960
Make an isolation zone there,

06:15.000 --> 06:16.640
keep them comfortable,
get them on fluids.

06:16.680 --> 06:19.760
There's some, uh, temporary
bedding in the truck.

06:19.800 --> 06:21.440
Okay.

06:21.480 --> 06:23.480
Have you done it before?

06:24.880 --> 06:28.120
Killed someone?

06:29.760 --> 06:32.000
I was a captain...

06:32.040 --> 06:35.920
in the Royal Artillery.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.800
When I was serving, they didn't
allow women near the front line,

06:37.840 --> 06:39.880
but they trusted
our tiny, female hands

06:39.920 --> 06:41.800
to get the same training
as everybody else, so.

06:43.840 --> 06:45.320
Lucky old us.

06:45.360 --> 06:47.400
You didn't answer my question.

06:51.640 --> 06:54.840
No, Tom, I've never killed
anyone before.

06:58.320 --> 07:00.040
I'll start bringing
the bedding in.

07:20.240 --> 07:21.760
[sighs]

07:21.800 --> 07:25.080
MARTIN: So Sankuru Airways
Flight 19.

07:25.120 --> 07:26.760
You survived the crash,
didn't you?

07:26.800 --> 07:30.400
-Mr. Arnason?
-How did you find me?

07:30.440 --> 07:32.160
There were 13 people
on that flight

07:32.200 --> 07:34.400
who were never positively
DNA matched

07:34.440 --> 07:35.840
with the remains found.

07:35.880 --> 07:38.440
We checked every one
of those names.

07:38.480 --> 07:42.000
Phone details.
Bank records.

07:42.040 --> 07:44.360
We found transactions
in your name.

07:44.400 --> 07:46.760
Big cash withdrawals,

07:46.800 --> 07:48.680
several days after the crash.

07:48.720 --> 07:51.680
The bank cancelled the card,

07:51.720 --> 07:54.280
assumed it had been stolen
somehow, but it was you,

07:54.320 --> 07:58.240
wasn't it, Mr. Arnason?

07:58.280 --> 08:01.320
It's been a long time since
I've been called that name.

08:03.360 --> 08:05.440
-We.
-Excuse me?

08:05.480 --> 08:06.840
You keep saying "we."

08:06.880 --> 08:08.360
"We found transactions
in your account."

08:08.400 --> 08:11.160
-Who is "we"?
-Myself, and, um,

08:11.200 --> 08:14.760
some people who used
to work for me.

08:14.800 --> 08:16.560
What kind of work are you in?

08:16.600 --> 08:19.360
I used to be in
military intelligence.

08:19.400 --> 08:21.400
Funny.

08:24.120 --> 08:25.600
I never talked about this,

08:25.640 --> 08:28.040
but now it seems I talk about it
all the time.

08:28.080 --> 08:30.480
But I am glad to.

08:30.520 --> 08:31.960
For so long,
this has held me down,

08:32.000 --> 08:34.200
the weight of what I know.

08:34.240 --> 08:36.680
Sometimes, at night, I...

08:36.720 --> 08:38.880
I can't catch my breath.

08:41.600 --> 08:43.240
Well, there was a man
on the flight.

08:43.280 --> 08:45.200
I'm s-- I'm sorry.

08:45.240 --> 08:46.360
I don't understand you.

08:46.400 --> 08:47.640
Aren't you here for me?

08:47.680 --> 08:50.840
You said you knew
what I'd done.

08:50.880 --> 08:54.520
Yes. But I don't care as long
as you tell me what happened.

08:54.560 --> 08:57.120
Now, there was a man
on the flight.

08:57.160 --> 08:58.800
Uh, mid-30s, white.

08:58.840 --> 09:01.840
Sorry. I... I don't remember.

09:01.880 --> 09:04.160
A regional flight from Goma
to Kinshasa,

09:04.200 --> 09:07.000
on any given day there'd be
no more than a handful

09:07.040 --> 09:09.560
of white people. Think.

09:09.600 --> 09:11.920
He might have been wearing
an orange baseball cap.

09:11.960 --> 09:15.400
Honestly, I-I try not to think
of it at all.

09:15.440 --> 09:19.320
When I do,
when the images come to me,

09:19.360 --> 09:21.240
they're blurry.

09:21.280 --> 09:23.680
I can't really place anything.

09:23.720 --> 09:25.920
Okay.

09:25.960 --> 09:27.560
Okay, never mind.

09:27.600 --> 09:31.800
[clears throat] Let's just talk
about the flight, hmm?

09:31.840 --> 09:34.160
[indistinct chatter]

09:35.520 --> 09:38.840
[Fabrice speaking Swahili]

09:38.880 --> 09:40.440
You took your time.

09:40.480 --> 09:42.240
Well, we had to let people know
that we were here.

09:42.280 --> 09:45.240
-Except the local headman
is nowhere to be found.
-Eh.

09:45.280 --> 09:47.360
-So there's nobody in charge?
-Not really.

09:47.400 --> 09:48.800
And the atmosphere out there,
it's not right.

09:48.840 --> 09:50.240
GEORGIA:
Why?

09:50.280 --> 09:52.040
-Because of the militia?
-No, it's not just them.

09:52.080 --> 09:53.440
It's something else.

09:53.480 --> 09:55.240
So let's keep our heads down
and finish our work.

09:55.280 --> 09:56.280
Well, we're ready.

09:56.320 --> 09:57.480
Perfect, then.

09:57.520 --> 09:58.520
Okay.

10:00.800 --> 10:02.720
[speaking Swahili]

10:11.520 --> 10:14.880
Ooh. [speaking Swahili]

10:30.640 --> 10:32.640
[Tom continues speaking Swahili]

10:47.720 --> 10:49.960
Hi. H-Have you seen this man
in this photo?

10:50.000 --> 10:51.200
[speaking Swahili]

10:51.240 --> 10:53.600
What the hell are you doing?

10:53.640 --> 10:55.040
Well, I just asked him if he's
seen the man in this photo.

10:55.080 --> 10:58.120
-No.
-[shouting in Swahili]

10:58.160 --> 11:00.280
-What's he saying?
-No. [speaking Swahili]

11:00.320 --> 11:02.560
-What's going on?
-I just asked him a question.

11:02.600 --> 11:03.920
I-I'm looking for somebody.

11:03.960 --> 11:05.360
Get out of here.

11:05.400 --> 11:06.920
-Get out of here.
-That man knows something!

11:06.960 --> 11:08.320
He-he recognizes
the person in this photo.

11:08.360 --> 11:10.040
-He can help me.
-I don't care.

11:10.080 --> 11:12.640
You wanted to come to Kisima?
You are here.

11:12.680 --> 11:15.640
But stay out of our way
while we are doing our jobs.

11:15.680 --> 11:17.040
-Do you understand that?
-Okay.

11:17.080 --> 11:18.920
-Sorry.
-Do you?

11:18.960 --> 11:22.000
-Go now!
-Yeah, okay. I'm sorry.

11:22.040 --> 11:24.560
-[whispers]: Calm down.
-[shouting in French]

11:28.600 --> 11:29.760
Ca va, ca va.

11:29.800 --> 11:31.360
Georgia--

11:34.080 --> 11:36.560
[shouting]

11:36.600 --> 11:39.000
[birds chirping]

11:52.840 --> 11:54.080
Hope you enjoyed the silence.

11:55.480 --> 11:57.440
Come on.
It's about to be broken.

12:00.360 --> 12:01.360
[exhales]

12:05.240 --> 12:07.760
[chanting]

12:36.160 --> 12:38.320
-You okay?
-[gasps]

12:40.040 --> 12:42.600
You know why I asked you
to kill that man?

12:43.640 --> 12:44.640
This is why.

12:44.680 --> 12:46.920
What we're about to do,

12:46.960 --> 12:48.280
it's serious.

12:48.320 --> 12:50.080
I need soldiers,

12:50.120 --> 12:51.640
not children.

12:51.680 --> 12:53.520
[man shouting]

12:53.560 --> 12:56.680
[chanting continues]

12:56.720 --> 12:59.280
[man shouting]

13:01.320 --> 13:04.280
[hisses sharply]

13:06.080 --> 13:07.760
[shouting, ululating]

13:07.800 --> 13:11.240
[sharp hissing, grunting]

13:11.280 --> 13:13.680
-[sound of rooster crowing]
-[sharp hissing]

13:19.800 --> 13:21.240
-DJAMBA: Mai-Mai!
-ALL: Mai!

13:21.280 --> 13:22.560
-Mai-Mai!
-Mai!

13:22.600 --> 13:25.280
[singing in Swahili]

13:25.320 --> 13:27.880
[group singing response
in Swahili]

13:27.920 --> 13:30.400
-[Djamba singing]
-[group singing response]

13:30.440 --> 13:32.840
[singing call and response]

13:49.960 --> 13:52.360
[call and response continues]

13:57.920 --> 14:00.360
[insects trilling]

14:00.400 --> 14:02.800
Excuse me,
have you seen this man?

14:04.920 --> 14:06.880
Sorry, ha-have you seen--

14:06.920 --> 14:09.400
have you seen this man here,
in this picture?

14:09.440 --> 14:10.720
Excuse me.

14:10.760 --> 14:13.240
Have you--
have you seen this man here?

14:15.240 --> 14:17.000
Do you recognize this man here?

14:17.040 --> 14:18.240
Mm-mm.

14:18.280 --> 14:19.760
[engine revving]

14:21.840 --> 14:24.520
[shouts in Swahili]

14:25.560 --> 14:27.840
[speaks Swahili]

14:27.880 --> 14:29.560
I'm sorry. I don't understand.

14:29.600 --> 14:31.120
What do you want?

14:31.160 --> 14:34.520
[speaking Swahili]

14:34.560 --> 14:36.600
I don't know what you're saying.
I'm sorry. I don't speak--

14:36.640 --> 14:38.360
What do you want?
[shouts]

14:38.400 --> 14:39.720
[shouts in Swahili]

14:39.760 --> 14:41.240
[groans, grunts]

14:41.280 --> 14:44.960
-[shouting in Swahili]
-[panting]

14:52.440 --> 14:55.280
[engine revving]

14:55.320 --> 14:57.520
[panting]

15:03.080 --> 15:05.680
-GEORGIA: Mm.
-[Will chuckles]

15:05.720 --> 15:07.520
-G-Get off.
-Hmm?

15:07.560 --> 15:10.000
-How could you say that to me?
-[chuckles]

15:10.040 --> 15:11.720
Your feet are freezing.
Get off.

15:11.760 --> 15:13.200
That's why you're here,
to warm them up.

15:13.240 --> 15:14.840
Oh, my God,
you're a bloody lizard.

15:14.880 --> 15:16.920
-You love lizards.
-Get off me, lizard.

15:16.960 --> 15:19.320
-You love lizards.
-I'm trying to sleep.

15:19.360 --> 15:21.280
[snorts]

15:21.320 --> 15:23.400
[sighs]

15:27.000 --> 15:28.520
It's ten past 8:00.

15:28.560 --> 15:30.080
-Really?
-Yeah.

15:30.120 --> 15:32.560
We must've tired her out
yesterday.

15:32.600 --> 15:34.160
She never sleeps this late.

15:34.200 --> 15:37.080
Maybe she's making up
for the last three months.

15:37.120 --> 15:39.880
Yeah, it's definitely on.

15:39.920 --> 15:41.800
I might go and check on her.

15:41.840 --> 15:43.360
No, no. I'll do it.

15:43.400 --> 15:44.760
-You sure?
-'Course.

15:44.800 --> 15:46.800
Keep your feet warm.

15:48.160 --> 15:50.760
[grunts]

15:50.800 --> 15:51.960
♪ Hey. ♪

15:52.000 --> 15:54.680
Sleepyhead?

15:54.720 --> 15:57.760
[over baby monitor]:
Hey, you...

15:57.800 --> 15:59.560
-[screams] Georgia!
-[gasps]

15:59.600 --> 16:02.960
WILL: Quickly! Georgia.
Georgia, she's not breathing.

16:03.000 --> 16:05.960
-She's not breathing!
Oh, my God.
-Violet!

16:06.000 --> 16:08.360
Violet, wake up!

16:08.400 --> 16:10.760
Will, call an ambulance.

16:10.800 --> 16:13.160
Oh, wake up. Wake up,
please, please, please.

16:13.200 --> 16:15.800
[crying]:
Wake up, Violet. Open your eyes.

16:15.840 --> 16:18.520
-Please, baby, please...
-She's three months old.

16:18.560 --> 16:20.400
GEORGIA [crying]:
Please open your eyes, Violet.

16:20.440 --> 16:23.400
Open them. Please.
[crying]

16:23.440 --> 16:26.720
-[Georgia sobbing]
-[Will speaking indistinctly]

16:26.760 --> 16:29.160
[children chattering, laughing]

16:42.640 --> 16:43.960
Any luck?

16:44.000 --> 16:46.120
No. Not yet.

16:47.320 --> 16:49.400
I'm good. I have some.
Thank you.

16:49.440 --> 16:51.520
I came to get that photo.
Offer my help.

16:51.560 --> 16:53.920
I'm don't think Louise
would approve of that, do you?

16:53.960 --> 16:55.720
[laughs]
Mm.

16:55.760 --> 16:58.120
Yeah, no,
she doesn't approve of much.

16:58.160 --> 17:01.400
But look, you helped me,
so... let me help you.

17:01.440 --> 17:03.320
You don't know the language.
I do.

17:03.360 --> 17:05.720
Look, I really don't want
to get you into trouble.

17:05.760 --> 17:07.120
I can handle Louise.

17:07.160 --> 17:09.160
It's not Louise. I just got
stopped by the militia.

17:09.200 --> 17:11.280
One of them threw me
on the ground.

17:11.320 --> 17:13.440
It's like they wanted something.

17:13.480 --> 17:16.240
His friend stopped him. And
he said something like, um...

17:16.280 --> 17:18.200
It was something like...

17:18.240 --> 17:21.280
-apana imagee?
-Uh-huh?

17:21.320 --> 17:23.840
Apana ima something?

17:23.880 --> 17:26.960
-S-- No, I'm s-- That
doesn't mean anything to me.
-No.

17:27.000 --> 17:28.680
That's not what he said. I-I
ca-- I-I wasn't paying attention

17:28.720 --> 17:29.800
'cause I didn't know
what they were gonna do.

17:29.840 --> 17:31.480
Well, all the more reason
to stick with us.

17:31.520 --> 17:32.920
You know?
Safety in numbers and all that.

17:32.960 --> 17:35.680
-It's...
-[speaking Swahili]

17:39.400 --> 17:41.920
She's asking
to see the-the photograph.

17:41.960 --> 17:43.320
The photograph of the man.

17:43.360 --> 17:44.880
Of course.

17:51.600 --> 17:53.600
Oui.

17:53.640 --> 17:55.640
[speaks Swahili]

17:55.680 --> 17:58.840
-TOM: She knows this man.
-[speaks Swahili]

17:58.880 --> 18:00.720
This man killed her husband.

18:00.760 --> 18:03.960
-Killed her husband?
-[speaks Swahili]

18:04.000 --> 18:05.960
He was here. Uh...

18:06.000 --> 18:08.200
[speaks Swahili]

18:08.240 --> 18:10.200
He came to this village a-a day

18:10.240 --> 18:13.680
or so ago, and he came with men.
Uh, soldiers, uh...

18:13.720 --> 18:16.080
[speaking Swahili]

18:19.560 --> 18:20.720
TOM:
The militia here are with him.

18:20.760 --> 18:22.920
[woman speaks Swahili]

18:22.960 --> 18:25.960
And they came
to kill her husband.

18:26.000 --> 18:28.440
This man, uh, Bello,

18:28.480 --> 18:30.320
he made a girl do it,
a-a young girl.

18:30.360 --> 18:32.280
Oh, God. Why?

18:32.320 --> 18:34.720
[speaking Swahili]

18:36.760 --> 18:39.160
There's a mine here.
A-a coltan mine.

18:39.200 --> 18:41.800
[speaks Swahili]

18:41.840 --> 18:44.040
So, her husband,

18:44.080 --> 18:45.480
he-he ran the, uh,

18:45.520 --> 18:47.760
the operations
for, uh, uh, Pieter Bello.

18:50.240 --> 18:55.360
The, uh... the mine that her
husband helped Pieter Bello run,

18:55.400 --> 18:57.320
where is it?

18:57.360 --> 18:59.760
[birds chirping]

19:04.800 --> 19:07.240
[man speaking indistinctly]

19:21.520 --> 19:22.520
[clinking]

19:27.160 --> 19:28.960
[man speaking indistinctly]

19:43.640 --> 19:46.640
-[gunfire]
-[screaming]

19:48.120 --> 19:50.640
-[shouting]
-[screaming]

19:50.680 --> 19:52.720
♪ ♪

19:52.760 --> 19:54.960
-[gunfire]
-[screaming]

20:08.080 --> 20:09.560
[crying]

20:19.600 --> 20:22.560
[exhales]

20:22.600 --> 20:25.000
[crying quietly]

20:26.200 --> 20:29.120
[crying]

20:29.160 --> 20:31.200
♪ ♪

20:43.240 --> 20:44.920
Listen, I appreciate it.

20:44.960 --> 20:47.520
You know I wouldn't ask
if it wasn't important, Tess.

20:47.560 --> 20:50.000
-Thank you. [sighs]
-[horn blows]

20:50.040 --> 20:51.800
MARTIN:
Well, this man's late 30s,

20:51.840 --> 20:54.160
-early 40s.
-Does he have the stars?

20:54.200 --> 20:55.600
Mr. Arnason.

20:55.640 --> 20:57.240
Please.

20:57.280 --> 20:59.200
Please stop calling me that.

20:59.240 --> 21:01.600
All right. Ariel.

21:01.640 --> 21:05.000
You described a man with two
gold stars on his epaulettes.

21:05.040 --> 21:06.600
You're sure about that,
are you not?

21:06.640 --> 21:08.880
Yes. Yes,
I remember that definitely.

21:08.920 --> 21:10.680
Well, then please assume
that I won't waste your time

21:10.720 --> 21:12.960
describing someone
who doesn't have that insignia.

21:13.000 --> 21:14.600
Okay.

21:14.640 --> 21:16.600
Heavy brows, brown eyes,

21:16.640 --> 21:19.360
thickset, his head's shaved.

21:19.400 --> 21:21.520
But, of course, he could've
had it, uh, cut before

21:21.560 --> 21:23.280
or after the...

21:23.320 --> 21:24.880
picture was taken.

21:24.920 --> 21:26.800
This is useless.
We've been through

21:26.840 --> 21:28.200
your list twice already.

21:28.240 --> 21:29.320
I don't know.

21:29.360 --> 21:30.400
But think.

21:30.440 --> 21:32.200
Even the tiniest
physical detail.

21:32.240 --> 21:34.840
You also saw him
in the newspaper.

21:34.880 --> 21:37.080
It wasn't a newspaper.
It was--

21:37.120 --> 21:39.800
They don't really have them
in that part of the Congo.

21:39.840 --> 21:41.040
It was...

21:41.080 --> 21:43.240
four sheets of home-printed A4.

21:43.280 --> 21:44.960
-It won't be on any record
anywhere.
-[sighs]

21:45.000 --> 21:48.000
-We're wasting our time.
-Mr. Arnason--

21:48.040 --> 21:50.200
uh, Ariel--

21:50.240 --> 21:52.840
you remember
the stars on the uniform.

21:52.880 --> 21:55.240
Now, the man you saw handing
what was a bomb

21:55.280 --> 21:58.280
to a woman on the plane
was a major general.

21:58.320 --> 22:00.280
Now, if you're right
about that insignia,

22:00.320 --> 22:01.600
he was in the Air Force.

22:01.640 --> 22:02.880
Now, that narrows

22:02.920 --> 22:05.760
our search down to 30,
maybe 40 men.

22:05.800 --> 22:07.560
Believe me, I want to help.

22:07.600 --> 22:09.280
Honestly.

22:09.320 --> 22:12.320
But I cannot identify a man
I can no longer see.

22:14.360 --> 22:16.840
Well...

22:16.880 --> 22:18.440
[sighs]

22:18.480 --> 22:20.200
Well, you have helped.

22:20.240 --> 22:23.280
Thanks to you, I now have more
information than I had before.

22:23.320 --> 22:25.880
And you believe me?

22:25.920 --> 22:27.920
Yes, I do.

22:31.760 --> 22:35.440
You say that.
Like it's so simple.

22:35.480 --> 22:37.840
But you know my real name.
You know what I've done.

22:37.880 --> 22:41.360
You had your reasons
for keeping your silence.

22:41.400 --> 22:43.840
Believe me, I understand.

22:43.880 --> 22:45.840
[chuckles]:
More than you could ever know.

22:45.880 --> 22:48.720
We make snap decisions.

22:48.760 --> 22:50.240
Fraction of a second.

22:50.280 --> 22:52.080
Then we have to live by them.

22:52.120 --> 22:54.200
All the messy consequences.

22:54.240 --> 22:56.560
Well, I appreciate your time.

22:56.600 --> 23:00.200
I have your number
if I need to talk to you again.

23:00.240 --> 23:02.240
What do I do now?

23:04.240 --> 23:06.640
Go home.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.960
[sighs]

23:13.000 --> 23:15.240
Just wait,
that's all I'm asking.

23:15.280 --> 23:16.640
Wait until I can come with you.

23:16.680 --> 23:18.360
Tom, trust me, I'll be fine.

23:18.400 --> 23:21.160
You can't go into the rain
forest by yourself, you lunatic.

23:21.200 --> 23:23.480
Look, please, I'm serious.

23:23.520 --> 23:24.760
It's not safe.

23:24.800 --> 23:26.520
Georgia. You...

23:26.560 --> 23:28.440
Please.

23:28.480 --> 23:30.320
Rule of thumb: you don't go off
anywhere out here on your own.

23:30.360 --> 23:32.040
Do you know where
that phrase comes from?

23:32.080 --> 23:34.480
There was this old English law

23:34.520 --> 23:37.080
that said a man could legally
beat his wife with a stick

23:37.120 --> 23:39.360
as long as the stick
was no thicker than his thumb.

23:39.400 --> 23:41.320
-Times have changed.
-Yeah.

23:41.360 --> 23:44.120
I can handle myself,
Tom, really.

23:44.160 --> 23:46.240
H-Hang on. Hang on.

23:46.280 --> 23:48.280
Oh, God.

23:50.440 --> 23:52.400
Look, I kept this.

23:52.440 --> 23:54.400
Um, do you want to take it?

23:54.440 --> 23:56.040
GEORGIA: I don't think
that's a good idea.

23:58.080 --> 24:01.240
-Better off
if they think I'm with you.
-Yes, yes, that's it.

24:01.280 --> 24:03.240
They should
leave a doctor alone.

24:03.280 --> 24:05.480
Should. I...

24:09.680 --> 24:13.520
You're walking towards a man
who had someone killed.

24:13.560 --> 24:15.600
And what you going to do
when you find him?

24:15.640 --> 24:17.960
[exhales]

24:18.000 --> 24:21.480
I'm going to ask him
where my husband is.

24:25.320 --> 24:27.280
Be careful.

24:27.320 --> 24:30.160
I think I'm way past that,
don't you?

24:59.320 --> 25:01.320
♪ ♪

25:26.680 --> 25:28.640
[door opens]

25:28.680 --> 25:30.680
[indistinct chatter on TV]

25:38.040 --> 25:41.440
-Hey.
-Hey.

25:44.040 --> 25:45.680
You were gone a while.

25:45.720 --> 25:48.240
Was I?

25:48.280 --> 25:50.320
One of these days
you're gonna go for a walk

25:50.360 --> 25:52.240
and not come back.

25:53.280 --> 25:54.840
Sorry.

25:54.880 --> 25:57.800
There's no need.

25:57.840 --> 25:59.920
All right?

25:59.960 --> 26:01.600
Hey.

26:01.640 --> 26:04.640
What the hell is this?

26:04.680 --> 26:07.680
It's estate agents
selling houses.

26:09.240 --> 26:12.240
I have no idea
why I watch this shit.

26:16.080 --> 26:17.960
Did you do this?

26:18.000 --> 26:21.000
Yeah. Sorry.

26:22.840 --> 26:25.800
You know, it calms me.

26:25.840 --> 26:28.600
For some reason.

26:28.640 --> 26:32.400
The way it calmed her
when you drew it on her back.

26:32.440 --> 26:35.080
I know it's stupid.

26:35.120 --> 26:37.200
It's not stupid.

26:39.200 --> 26:40.480
Hey.

26:40.520 --> 26:42.040
You know,
Angela said she'd see you.

26:42.080 --> 26:44.560
-Whenever you want.
-Therapy's not gonna help.

26:44.600 --> 26:45.880
That guy you saw

26:45.920 --> 26:48.960
with your parents,
he was no good.

26:49.000 --> 26:50.960
Not all therapists are the same.

26:51.000 --> 26:53.880
-They can't say anything.
-It's not about what they say.

26:53.920 --> 26:56.360
Georgia, it's about you...

26:56.400 --> 26:59.600
just saying anything.

26:59.640 --> 27:02.120
Like what?

27:03.120 --> 27:05.400
It's been six months.

27:05.440 --> 27:07.080
We have to try
and live our lives.

27:07.120 --> 27:09.120
We have to try.

27:11.120 --> 27:13.800
[sighs]

27:36.480 --> 27:38.480
[indistinct chatter]

28:05.040 --> 28:07.040
♪ ♪

28:23.040 --> 28:25.320
[gun clicks]

28:36.040 --> 28:38.040
[speaking Swahili]

28:40.440 --> 28:42.320
Who are you?

28:42.360 --> 28:44.920
I'm a doctor.

28:47.360 --> 28:49.320
Come.

28:49.360 --> 28:51.000
Move.

29:05.120 --> 29:07.680
Look, I'm no threat
to you or anybody.

29:07.720 --> 29:09.680
If you just let me go,
I won't cause any trouble.

29:12.000 --> 29:13.280
[Sadiki groans]

29:14.560 --> 29:16.560
[inhales sharply]

29:20.600 --> 29:22.600
Move. He needs your help.

29:22.640 --> 29:23.760
[speaking Swahili]

29:43.640 --> 29:44.920
It's a bullet wound.

29:44.960 --> 29:46.200
Yes.

29:47.720 --> 29:50.680
[Sadiki groans]

29:50.720 --> 29:52.200
[screams]

29:52.240 --> 29:54.040
[speaks Swahili]

29:54.080 --> 29:55.720
[Adidja speaks Swahili]

29:58.440 --> 30:00.000
There's a...

30:00.040 --> 30:01.800
there's fragments of bullet
still left in there.

30:01.840 --> 30:03.200
We need to get them out.

30:10.120 --> 30:12.520
He says okay.

30:12.560 --> 30:13.960
[gasps]

30:14.000 --> 30:16.120
[Sadiki screams]

30:16.160 --> 30:18.160
Sorry. Sorry.

30:22.000 --> 30:24.160
[Sadiki groaning]

30:38.000 --> 30:39.920
What was that about?

30:39.960 --> 30:41.960
Asking how long
we were going to be here.

30:42.000 --> 30:43.360
Why?

30:43.400 --> 30:45.600
I did not wait to find out.

30:48.640 --> 30:50.600
My throat feels like sandpaper.

30:50.640 --> 30:52.320
You need to drink more.

30:52.360 --> 30:53.800
You need to talk less.

30:53.840 --> 30:56.240
-But we can't have everything,
can we?
-[chuckles]

30:56.280 --> 30:58.320
Oh, Louise. You ever think
about being, I don't know...

30:58.360 --> 31:00.120
-a nicer person?
-Ooh.

31:00.160 --> 31:01.960
It is not about being nice.

31:02.000 --> 31:04.280
There are simply
more important things in life.

31:04.320 --> 31:07.200
And anyway, I'm nice.
I'm here, aren't I?

31:07.240 --> 31:10.360
Just because you do good things
doesn't make you a nice person.

31:10.400 --> 31:12.680
But doing bad things
makes you a bad person,

31:12.720 --> 31:15.480
so I don't see why not.

31:15.520 --> 31:18.960
We're done here.
We should get going.

31:19.000 --> 31:20.880
We're not scheduled
to move on until tomorrow.

31:20.920 --> 31:22.760
With the militia around?

31:22.800 --> 31:24.480
I'd rather not wait.

31:24.520 --> 31:25.880
Well...

31:25.920 --> 31:27.560
-What?
-What about Georgia?

31:27.600 --> 31:29.560
What about her?

31:29.600 --> 31:31.760
The woman lied
about who she was.

31:31.800 --> 31:34.200
-Okay.
-She shot a man in front of us.

31:34.240 --> 31:36.200
-She's our responsibility.
-Mm-hmm.

31:36.240 --> 31:38.200
She wanted a ride out here.

31:38.240 --> 31:39.520
-She got one.
-[sighs]

31:39.560 --> 31:41.640
She's more than capable
of taking care of herself.

31:41.680 --> 31:44.720
-We've all seen that.
-Well, we can't just
leave her out there.

31:44.760 --> 31:46.960
Why?

31:48.000 --> 31:50.480
Why are you so keen to move on?

31:52.800 --> 31:56.440
Because otherwise we are
just standing still, aren't we?

32:00.480 --> 32:02.040
Love you.

32:02.080 --> 32:03.680
Fuck you.

32:03.720 --> 32:06.120
[Fabrice chuckles]

32:06.160 --> 32:09.120
You have to keep it clean.

32:09.160 --> 32:11.200
Change this every day, each day.

32:11.240 --> 32:13.880
And, um, take one of these.
One in the morning

32:13.920 --> 32:15.880
and once in the evening, okay?

32:15.920 --> 32:18.080
I understand. I tell him.

32:18.120 --> 32:19.240
[speaking Swahili]

32:24.840 --> 32:27.480
Apana hivo. Ingine. Ingine.

32:27.520 --> 32:29.880
-What did you say?
-He confuses.

32:29.920 --> 32:33.480
He thinks bandages twice a day,
pills once.

32:33.520 --> 32:35.840
-I tell him no, the other one.
-But you said, um...

32:35.880 --> 32:39.280
-"Apana hivo. Ingine"?
-Yes.

32:39.320 --> 32:41.640
This means,
"You've got it wrong.

32:41.680 --> 32:44.480
The other one."

32:44.520 --> 32:47.120
[man speaking Swahili]

32:47.160 --> 32:49.000
You go now.

32:52.280 --> 32:54.240
-Eh!
-Not that way.

32:54.280 --> 32:55.840
I need to talk to Pieter Bello.

32:55.880 --> 32:57.640
Militia everywhere that way.

32:57.680 --> 32:59.680
Go back to where you came from.

33:06.760 --> 33:09.320
[insects trilling,
birds singing]

33:12.280 --> 33:14.560
Decided to come back then?

33:14.600 --> 33:16.520
You're "the other one,"
aren't you?

33:16.560 --> 33:18.760
-They were looking for you.
-What are you talking about?

33:18.800 --> 33:20.200
"Apana hivo. Ingine."

33:20.240 --> 33:22.240
The militia guy.

33:22.280 --> 33:24.320
He said, "You got it wrong.
The other one."

33:24.360 --> 33:25.720
They were talking about you.

33:25.760 --> 33:27.120
That's bullshit.

33:27.160 --> 33:28.800
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

33:28.840 --> 33:30.760
All right, let's go ask them.

33:30.800 --> 33:32.560
-Come on.
-Hey, stop! Stop!

33:32.600 --> 33:34.080
-Let's go.
-Okay, okay.

33:34.120 --> 33:35.600
You want to know.
Okay, poutin.

33:38.040 --> 33:40.040
My mother has dementia.

33:40.080 --> 33:42.400
Round the clock care she needs.
She deserves it,

33:42.440 --> 33:44.680
and no one else can pay,
so, one day,

33:44.720 --> 33:46.880
someone comes to me,
they offer me money.

33:46.920 --> 33:48.240
What am I supposed to do?

33:48.280 --> 33:49.640
They offered you money for what?

33:49.680 --> 33:51.040
You've heard of coltan?

33:51.080 --> 33:52.920
It's in every smartphone,
laptop...

33:52.960 --> 33:55.480
Yeah, I've heard of colton.
There's a mine north of here.

33:55.520 --> 33:56.920
Owned by the government,

33:56.960 --> 33:58.360
so, whenever I come
through these parts,

33:58.400 --> 34:00.160
I load up one of the vehicles
with coltan

34:00.200 --> 34:01.880
and take it across the border
to Rwanda.

34:01.920 --> 34:05.760
You do what I do, the border
guards tend to leave you alone.

34:05.800 --> 34:07.840
Yeah. No sense harassing
the good guys, right?

34:07.880 --> 34:11.120
Fuck you. I love what I do,
but I'm paid nothing.

34:11.160 --> 34:14.480
So, yes, I guess I'm a bad
person who does good things.

34:14.520 --> 34:16.000
What did the militia want
with you?

34:16.040 --> 34:17.600
They wanted me to go to the mine

34:17.640 --> 34:19.120
and meet with Pieter Bello.

34:19.160 --> 34:20.640
How do you know him?

34:20.680 --> 34:22.760
He's the one who paid me.
He's the one

34:22.800 --> 34:25.040
-smuggling the coltan
out of the mine.
-But you knew

34:25.080 --> 34:27.320
I was looking for him! You saw
the photo, you said nothing.

34:27.360 --> 34:30.200
Why should I? I don't know you.
I don't owe you a thing.

34:30.240 --> 34:32.320
He knows where my husband is.
Will Mason.

34:32.360 --> 34:34.280
-You heard that name before?
-Nothing.

34:34.320 --> 34:36.360
I swear, I met Pieter
a few times, at most.

34:36.400 --> 34:38.560
He came to me, made me an offer,
I said yes.

34:38.600 --> 34:40.080
That's it.
I've told you what I know.

34:40.120 --> 34:42.680
-So, where are you going?
-Get some rest.

34:42.720 --> 34:45.240
We need to get moving
tomorrow at first light.

34:45.280 --> 34:47.280
-No. Hold on.
-What?

34:47.320 --> 34:48.680
You need to do something for me.

34:48.720 --> 34:49.960
Like what?

34:50.000 --> 34:51.920
Help me get to Pieter Bello.

34:51.960 --> 34:54.040
Why should I help you?

34:54.080 --> 34:55.960
Because he knows
where my husband is.

34:56.000 --> 34:57.920
You're asking the wrong person.

34:57.960 --> 34:59.560
I have my own problem, Georgia.

34:59.600 --> 35:01.200
You know what?
I'm your problem now.

35:01.240 --> 35:03.120
If you don't want me
to start telling the people

35:03.160 --> 35:04.720
that you work for
what you've been up to,

35:04.760 --> 35:06.600
then you're gonna do what I say.
Do you understand?

35:08.920 --> 35:10.920
[indistinct chatter]

35:11.920 --> 35:14.840
[footsteps approaching]

35:17.400 --> 35:19.480
Mr. Helgason?

35:19.520 --> 35:21.640
The front desk told me
you were here.

35:21.680 --> 35:24.160
-It's Martin.
-I recognized the footsteps.

35:24.200 --> 35:27.200
Your posh English shoes.
You could tap-dance in those.

35:27.240 --> 35:29.120
Hmm.

35:29.160 --> 35:31.760
I'm sorry. I'm confused.
Why are you here?

35:31.800 --> 35:33.240
It's just that...

35:33.280 --> 35:35.840
It's just that now,
between meeting Beatrix

35:35.880 --> 35:38.720
and then you turning up here...

35:38.760 --> 35:41.600
If there is a God, then he is
trying to speak to me.

35:41.640 --> 35:43.880
And it's not just a sign.
It's a handwritten invitation.

35:43.920 --> 35:45.720
An invitation to what?

35:45.760 --> 35:48.320
To the DRC. I want to come
with you to Kinshasa.

35:48.360 --> 35:50.680
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Just a minute.

35:50.720 --> 35:53.400
Ariel, come with me a minute.

35:53.440 --> 35:56.640
[indistinct chatter]

35:56.680 --> 35:58.840
This is not an option.

35:58.880 --> 36:00.600
I remember his voice.

36:00.640 --> 36:03.400
The man
who gave that woman the laptop.

36:03.440 --> 36:04.840
I remember it
as clear as anything.

36:04.880 --> 36:06.960
We go out there,
and you can narrow down the list

36:07.000 --> 36:08.320
of people it might be.

36:08.360 --> 36:09.760
I can listen to his voice.

36:09.800 --> 36:11.680
Ariel, this is madness.

36:11.720 --> 36:14.000
Look, I'm not proud
of the man I used to be.

36:14.040 --> 36:16.640
You want to find
your friend's husband. Me?

36:16.680 --> 36:18.840
I just want to do what I should
have done a long time ago.

36:18.880 --> 36:22.200
I want this man
who downed that airplane,

36:22.240 --> 36:24.080
who murdered all those people,
to be brought to justice.

36:24.120 --> 36:26.440
Yeah,
why didn't you just say that?

36:26.480 --> 36:28.160
[laughs]

36:28.200 --> 36:30.160
-Yeah, you're right.
-Hmm.

36:30.200 --> 36:32.560
I-I have no proof
of what happened.

36:32.600 --> 36:34.920
-I only have my word.
-Hmm.

36:34.960 --> 36:38.080
And how is your going to
Kinshasa going to change that?

36:38.120 --> 36:40.120
I-I can sit with him.

36:40.160 --> 36:42.320
I can sit with him--
this man, this general.

36:42.360 --> 36:43.920
[clears throat]
Ariel...?

36:43.960 --> 36:46.360
He executed a plane
full of innocent people.

36:46.400 --> 36:48.480
And when he finds out I exist,

36:48.520 --> 36:51.240
he won't hesitate
try and do the same with me.

36:51.280 --> 36:53.480
Oh, so you just want
to make yourself bait

36:53.520 --> 36:55.120
for a mass murderer?

36:55.160 --> 36:58.840
Yes. I wish to atone.

36:58.880 --> 37:00.880
Hmm.

37:00.920 --> 37:02.520
Please.

37:02.560 --> 37:04.160
TOM:
I had no

37:04.200 --> 37:06.640
idea what she was doing.

37:06.680 --> 37:09.280
But whenever we were in Goma,

37:09.320 --> 37:11.600
she would always pop over
the Rwandan border to Giseny.

37:11.640 --> 37:14.080
Said she was seeing someone.
I...

37:14.120 --> 37:17.440
Believe me, please, if I had
any thought that she was...

37:17.480 --> 37:19.600
You didn't know.
It wasn't your fault.

37:19.640 --> 37:24.560
Oh, you think you know someone,
but you never can tell, can you?

37:24.600 --> 37:27.120
Take you, for example.

37:27.160 --> 37:28.680
I mean, no offense, but I never
would have taken you

37:28.720 --> 37:30.640
for an army captain.

37:33.840 --> 37:36.640
You're gonna be okay, right?

37:40.680 --> 37:43.480
Sure, yeah.

37:43.520 --> 37:45.600
[insects trilling,
birds singing]

38:10.760 --> 38:12.760
[tools clanking]

38:15.320 --> 38:16.600
[speaking Swahili]

38:16.640 --> 38:19.640
Louise Chartrain.
Pieter Bello is expecting me.

38:19.680 --> 38:21.040
[speaking Swahili]

38:21.080 --> 38:23.680
[speaks Swahili]

38:31.880 --> 38:33.920
[speaking Swahili]

38:37.280 --> 38:39.280
Sit down.

38:40.480 --> 38:41.960
She's here.

38:42.000 --> 38:44.840
PIETER:
Okay.

38:48.840 --> 38:50.840
Ingia.

38:55.120 --> 38:57.640
[door squeaks shut]

39:00.120 --> 39:04.120
-Louise. How are you?
-I've been better.

39:04.160 --> 39:06.920
-I'm sorry to hear that.
-I was sorry to hear

39:06.960 --> 39:09.920
that you shot the man who runs
your operations for you here.

39:09.960 --> 39:13.400
Kalehe.
He didn't run anything.

39:13.440 --> 39:15.360
He ran his mouth off.

39:15.400 --> 39:18.000
Nothing for you to worry about.

39:18.040 --> 39:22.200
And how do I know you are not
going to do the same to me?

39:22.240 --> 39:24.840
That's what I want
to talk to you about.

39:24.880 --> 39:27.960
There's been a change
of ownership.

39:28.000 --> 39:30.360
I'm running this place now.

39:30.400 --> 39:33.360
As far as we're concerned,
nothing changes.

39:33.400 --> 39:36.080
If you're near, we'll arrange

39:36.120 --> 39:39.240
a trip for you to Rwanda
in a nice, decent-sized vehicle.

39:39.280 --> 39:41.840
I don't know. I feel like
it's getting out of control.

39:41.880 --> 39:45.280
The trouble has passed,
I promise you.

39:53.400 --> 39:57.280
You know there is a white woman
in Kisima asking about you.

40:00.160 --> 40:02.520
-What woman?
-Georgia Wells.

40:02.560 --> 40:06.600
She is looking for you
and a man called Will.

40:06.640 --> 40:09.040
And she's in Kisima now?

40:09.080 --> 40:10.440
I just left her there.

40:10.480 --> 40:12.600
You head back there
right now,

40:12.640 --> 40:15.840
and you make sure
she doesn't leave.

40:18.120 --> 40:21.280
You keep up this kind of work

40:21.320 --> 40:22.720
and you have nothing
to worry about.

40:22.760 --> 40:25.480
I hope so.

40:41.280 --> 40:44.640
There's a white woman in Kisima
I need you to take care of.

40:44.680 --> 40:46.160
Take five men with you.

40:51.520 --> 40:53.920
I did it.

40:53.960 --> 40:56.160
I just hope your man Will
is worth it.

41:12.080 --> 41:14.080
WILL [whispering]:
Georgie.

41:14.120 --> 41:16.360
[Georgia exhales]

41:29.520 --> 41:33.080
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

41:33.120 --> 41:35.800
No, no, no.
Don't cry, you're okay.

41:38.560 --> 41:41.760
-Oh, God, you must hate me.
-No.

41:41.800 --> 41:45.960
No. No, I don't hate you.

41:46.000 --> 41:48.400
I'm bloody furious
at you, though.

41:48.440 --> 41:51.560
That you thought that
this was somehow...

41:51.600 --> 41:54.640
I didn't plan it.
I just...

41:57.760 --> 42:00.720
I just...
It just hit me all at once

42:00.760 --> 42:03.200
that I was never gonna
see her again. [sniffles]

42:03.240 --> 42:07.120
Just promise me never again.
Okay?

42:07.160 --> 42:10.560
I'm here, Georgie.

42:10.600 --> 42:15.400
The two of us,
we need to stay together.

42:15.440 --> 42:18.440
We're all we have.

42:21.240 --> 42:23.440
[whispering]:
I love you, Georgie.

42:23.480 --> 42:25.480
You'll be okay, all right?

42:41.320 --> 42:43.000
[man shouting in Swahili]

43:09.640 --> 43:12.920
[insects buzzing]

43:39.960 --> 43:41.960
♪ ♪

43:59.640 --> 44:01.640
[door creaks open]

44:08.480 --> 44:11.680
What have you done
with my husband?

44:14.680 --> 44:16.680
♪ ♪

44:43.360 --> 44:45.360
♪ ♪
